944706f7-1803-4d15-8d6f-69d2bc598da8	Ministry Resources Manager	**Reports to:** Operations/Technology Leadership. \r\n\r\n# Goal\r\nEnsure all church partners have appropriate access to Communio Toolbox resources aligned with their roles and responsibilities for optimal ministry support. \r\n\r\n# Key Responsibilities\r\n-  **Account Creation & Management:** Receive requests from CSS with complete user information (first name, last name, email address, role designation), create appropriate access levels based on role requirements, coordinate with CSS for secure credential distribution. \r\n- **Role-Based Access Management:** \r\n  - **Pastor accounts:** Full access to all resources, strategic planning tools, advanced ministry materials. \r\n  - **RCT Leader accounts:** Team leadership access including event planning, volunteer coordination, ministry execution resources. \r\n  - **Staff accounts:** Ministry-specific access tailored to their departmental responsibilities and involvement level. \r\n  - **Volunteer accounts:** Limited access focused on their specific ministry tasks and training materials. \r\n- **Quality Assurance:** Verify all email addresses are valid and verified before account creation, ensure role designations align with church organizational structure, maintain account security and access integrity. \r\n- **Response Standards:**\r\n  - **Processing Time:** Complete account creation within 24 hours of receiving complete request information. \r\n  - **Coordination:** Work directly with CSS to ensure timely credential delivery and any necessary access modifications. \r\n- **Documentation:** Maintain accurate records of all account creations, access level assignments, and modification history.\r\n# Meeting Rhythms\r\n- Weekly coordination with CSS team for account requests\r\n- Monthly access review and system updates\r\n- Quarterly security and permissions audit.	59750382-b98f-4160-a00e-a1b2660d723a
b3e1d087-12e6-41e4-80de-870fefbe1ea0	VP of Church Strategy	**Reports to:** Executive Leadership.\r\n# Goal\r\nProvide strategic oversight of all church partnerships, ensure optimal team performance, and guide organizational growth initiatives in church relationship ministry. \r\n# Key Responsibilities\r\n- **Strategic Leadership:** Determine coaching models and scalability for Group SPVs based on church participation numbers (1-7 churches: Strategist Coaching, 8-14 churches: Church Facilitator Coaching, 15-21 churches: Advanced Facilitator model, 21+ requires custom approval). Oversee church ownership assignments and transitions in Salesforce ensuring optimal CES/CSS pairings. Provide strategic guidance for complex church situations requiring escalation beyond individual strategist capacity. - - **Team Management:** Manage CES and CSS assignments based on capacity, expertise, and church needs. Conduct regular performance reviews and professional development planning. Coordinate team communication protocols and ensure collaboration effectiveness. \r\n- **Operational Oversight:** Monitor organizational KPIs including Recipe Scores, Strategist Satisfaction ratings, and church retention metrics. Guide strategic adjustments based on performance data and market feedback. Approve complex grant funding decisions and resource allocations. \r\n# Meeting Rhythms\r\n- Weekly leadership team meetings\r\n- Monthly team performance reviews\r\n- Quarterly strategic planning sessions with executive team\r\n- Semi-annual church portfolio assessments\r\n# Performance Standards \r\n- Maintain team Strategist Satisfaction scores above 90%\r\n- Ensure optimal church assignment distributions\r\n- Guide strategic initiatives supporting organizational growth targets	59750382-b98f-4160-a00e-a1b2660d723a
6b780276-e913-4acc-a756-130b219ce179	Church Success Specialist	**Reports to:** Director of Church Success. \r\n**Revised:** October 8, 2024. \r\n\r\n# Goal\r\nProvide expert consultative services that guide church clients toward achieving their mission outcomes while fostering strong satisfaction and advocacy for Communio. Support the CES during onboarding and ensure ongoing client success through continuous engagement and troubleshooting. \r\n\r\n# Key Responsibilities\r\n- **Support Church Onboarding:** \r\n  - Collaboration with CES - Work alongside the CES to execute the onboarding plan and incorporate agreed-upon adjustments. \r\n  - Proactive Communication: Share observations and insights with the CES during weekly meetings or as necessary. \r\n- **Provide Strategic Consulting and Implementation Support:** \r\n  - **Build Strong Relationships:** Cultivate meaningful connections with church leaders, particularly the RCT Leader and Pastor. Strengthen relationships through thoughtful outreach (e.g., handwritten notes, small gifts). \r\n  - **Monitor Mission Plan Execution:** Support church leaders in executing their Mission Plan through monthly check-ins and strategic coaching. Utilize Communio tools like the Ministry Engagement Ladder, the Communio Playbook, and the Online Toolbox to guide leaders in their relationship ministry efforts. \r\n  - **Track mission objectives and KPIs:** Sunday attendance growth, event participation rates, engagement in growth journeys (8+ hours relationship enrichment per individual). \r\n    - **Performance threshold:** Churches must maintain at least 60% green recipe score meeting activity benchmarks. Scores below 60% trigger immediate CES involvement for troubleshooting and strategic intervention. \r\n- **Troubleshoot Challenges and Ensure Success:** \r\n  - **Identify and Address Issues:** \r\n    - **Monitor church progress** and proactively address concerns before they escalate. \r\n    - **WARNING SIGNS:** Declining Recipe Scores, missed Mission Plan activities, lack of Growth Journey participation (8+ hours), declining attendance data. \r\n  - **Escalate significant challenges** to the CES and collaborate on solutions.   \r\n    - **ESCALATION TRIGGERS:** Recipe Scores below 60%, Net Detractor scores (1-6), non-functioning RCT teams, vision drift indicators. \r\n- **Ensure Ongoing Church Success:** Respond to client inquiries within one business day, ensuring timely and effective support. Maintain high service standards so church leaders feel consistently supported. \r\n- **Collaborate with CES:** \r\n  - **Maintain Ongoing Communication:** Provide CES with regular updates on church progress and evolving needs. Partner with CES to facilitate additional training or development as needed (e.g., Culture Index training, volunteer recruitment, custom support). \r\n\r\n# Performance KPIs\r\n- **Mission Achievement:** Churches establish and maintain a Mission Plan aligned with their long-term goals. \r\n- **Performance Metrics:** \r\n  - **Maintain at least 60% green recipe score** for assigned churches, meeting activity benchmarks. \r\n  - **Escalation threshold:** Any church scoring below 60% requires immediate action plan development with CES involvement. \r\n  - Track monthly Recipe Score updates (0-100 point scale) across Vision, Community, Skills, and Leadership criteria. \r\n- **Satisfaction and Advocacy:** **Sustain 90% Strategist Satisfaction Score** - measured through pastor feedback forms. \r\n  - **Target threshold:** 90% positive scores required for performance standards. \r\n  - **Maintain strong Net Promoter Score (NPS)** reflecting client satisfaction. \r\n  - **Scoring criteria:** Target scores of 9-10 (Net Promoters), avoid scores of 1-6 (Net Detractors), monitor scores of 7-8 (passive). Any Net Detractor scores require immediate CES and CSS review with action plan development. \r\n- **Proactive Support:** Address challenges early and collaborate with CES to determine necessary interventions. \r\n\r\n# Meeting Rhythms\r\n- **Monthly meetings with RCT Leader** - Provide a personal check-in, review the upcoming calendar, share resources and suggestions, and address ideas or issues raised by the RCT Leader. A monthly meeting can also incorporate an event debrief if the timing is appropriate. \r\n- **Weekly CSS meetings** - Team coordination and case management. **Monthly Recipe Score reviews** with CES - Identify focus areas for the coming month and determine if CES support is needed to troubleshoot challenges.\r\n\r\n# Communication Standards\r\n## Response Times\r\n- Respond to individual or small group messages immediately if possible, or within a maximum of 4 hours (same day).\r\n- Acknowledge team board messages within 24 hours.\r\n- Respond to external-facing or project-based items within a maximum of 24 hours.\r\n## Meeting Expectations\r\n- Weekly team meetings: The Church Strategist team meets weekly on Mondays following an alternating rhythm between full team meetings and role-specific (CES/CSS) meetings.\r\n- Weekly one-on-one meetings: Each Church Strategist meets weekly with their manager for ongoing support, coaching, and accountability following a structured weekly and monthly rhythm.\r\n## Internal Meeting Protocols\r\n- Arrive on Time: Punctuality shows mutual respect.\r\n- Be Fully Present: No multitasking unless emergency.\r\n- Name Waste, Honor Purpose: Address concerns one-on-one with meeting leader.	59750382-b98f-4160-a00e-a1b2660d723a
ce6022e2-fe69-401b-86c2-3509aee52cb9	Growth Team Representative	**Reports to:** VP of Growth/Sales. \r\n\r\n# Goal\r\nEnsure seamless transition from sales to onboarding while maintaining relationship continuity and strategic context for optimal church partner success.\r\n\r\n# Key Responsibilities\r\n- **Contract Transition Management:** Send introductory emails to pastors within 24 hours of contract signature including introduction to assigned CES and CSS, explanation of next steps, 2-3 potential meeting time options for Welcome & Orientation call, clear call-to-action for scheduling. \r\n- **Team Briefing Coordination:** Schedule coordinated briefing meetings with CES and CSS teams within 24-48 hours after research completion. Provide comprehensive sales context including church leadership personalities, key motivations/concerns discussed during sales process, special commitments made, timeline expectations, strategic handoff coordination. \r\n- **Strategic Support:** May request CES attendance at end-of-sales-cycle meetings to answer clarifying questions and explain partnership details. Coordinate with VP of Church Strategy for CES assignment clarification when needed. \r\n\r\n# Performance Standards\r\n- **Response Time:** 24-hour maximum for pastor introductions, 48-hour maximum for team coordination.\r\n- **Follow-up Protocol:** If no pastor response within 48 hours, send follow-up email and consider phone call within 72 hours. \r\n- **Documentation:** Send meeting summaries to participants within 24 hours with key action items and responsibilities confirmed. \r\n\r\n# Meeting Rhythms\r\n- Weekly sales team meetings\r\n- Monthly handoff coordination reviews with Church Strategy team\r\n- Quarterly pipeline and conversion analysis sessions	59750382-b98f-4160-a00e-a1b2660d723a
a25abb58-f3b2-4ec8-b232-780d53d3c129	Church Engagement Specialist	Reports to: Vice President of Church Strategy. \nRevised: March 11, 2025. \n\n# Goal\nThe Church Engagement Specialist (CES) plays a critical role in ensuring church clients have an outstanding experience working with Communio. The goal is to create "raving fans", or churches that are excited about their partnership, eager to share their success, and willing to advocate for Communio. The CES ensures that every church: \n  1. Has an amazing onboarding experience, feeling connected, excited, and clear about their next steps. \n  2. Remains engaged and enthusiastic about their work with Communio, demonstrating strong buy-in and execution. \n  3. Becomes an advocate for Communio, willingly sharing their positive experiences with prospective churches. \n\n# Key Responsibilities: \n## Own the Onboarding Process\nLead the onboarding experience for new church clients, ensuring it is seamless, engaging, and effective. Partner with the Church Success Specialist (CSS) but take full ownership to drive the onboarding process. Maintain a structured onboarding process, but tailor it as needed to meet the unique needs of each church. Capture feedback to continuously improve the onboarding experience. \n## Facilitate the Relationship with the CSS\nBuild a trusted working relationship with the CSS, staying available and supportive. Take the initiative to meet regularly with the CSS, discussing challenges and identifying solutions. Proactively collaborate with the CSS to ensure church clients receive ongoing support. Share insights from your relationship with the pastor that will help the CSS be more effective in their job.\n## Ensure Ongoing Buy-In of Church Clients\nKeep a pulse on the level of church engagement and enthusiasm for the partnership. Identify early signs of disengagement and intervene with proactive solutions. These early signs could come from the pastor or the observations of the CSS. Offer additional training, resources, or encouragement when churches face challenges. Troubleshoot roadblocks to help churches sustain momentum in their plans. Champion church success by recognizing and celebrating wins along the way. Give special focus to sharing these with the pastor. \n## Shepherd the Pastor \nDevelop and maintain the primary relationship with the Lead Pastor/Priest at each church. Maintain consistent touchpoints (calls, emails, texts, in-person visits) to nurture trust and engagement. Offer both personal and professional support, ensuring pastors feel cared for and equipped. Help pastors cast a compelling vision for their congregations and teams. Proactively look for ways to add unexpected value to their work. \n## Support the Expansion of Communio's Work\nWhile not responsible for sales, support the Growth Team by: Securing referrals from pastors who are enthusiastic about their partnership. Facilitating introductions and connections between existing and prospective church clients. Occasionally joining sales calls or meetings to provide real-world insight into Communio's impact. \n \n# Performance KPIs\n- **Successful Onboarding Experiences:** Measured by the formation of a Relationship Culture Team, creation of a Mission Plan, and scores on the onboarding survey at the end of the process. Churches should feel excited, confident, and clear about their partnership. \n- **Churches with Strong Buy-In:** Measured by execution of planned activities and a positive Net Promoter Score (NPS) on pastor feedback forms. Churches should remain highly engaged and committed to their Mission Plans. \n- **Happy & Supported Pastors:** Measured by **90% positive "Strategist Score"** on pastor feedback forms. \n  - **Performance threshold:** Must maintain 90% positive scores consistently. Pastors should feel well cared for, supported, and equipped in their work. \n  - **Escalation criteria:** Scores below 90% require immediate review and intervention strategy development. \n- **Strong CSS Collaboration:** Measured by feedback from CSS team members to managers. The CES should be responsive, proactive, and effective in supporting the CSS. \n- **Tangible Expansion & Advocacy:** Measured by referrals, introductions, and Growth Team support efforts. A successful CES helps increase Communio's impact through strong church advocacy. \n \n# Meeting Rhythms\n- **Monthly touchpoints with pastors and leaders** - Each CES is responsible for maintaining and logging monthly touchpoints with senior pastors and key leaders at their assigned churches. \n- **Quarterly meetings with Lead Pastor** - Focus on relational care, early signs of disengagement, and vision alignment. Include: Personal and spiritual check-in, review of key ministry wins and challenges, discuss team engagement and any roadblocks, offer encouragement, training, or resources, align on vision and goals for the next quarter, explore growth opportunities or referrals.\n\n# Communication Standards\n## Response Times\n- Respond to individual or small group messages immediately if possible, or within a maximum of 4 hours (same day).\n- Acknowledge team board messages within 24 hours.\n- Respond to external-facing or project-based items within a maximum of 24 hours.\n\n## Meeting Expectations\n- Weekly team meetings: The Church Strategist team meets weekly on Mondays following an alternating rhythm between full team meetings and role-specific (CES/CSS) meetings.\n- Weekly one-on-one meetings: Each Church Strategist meets weekly with their manager for ongoing support, coaching, and accountability following a structured weekly and monthly rhythm.\n\n## Internal Meeting Protocols\n- Arrive on Time: Punctuality shows mutual respect.\n- Be Fully Present: No multitasking unless emergency.\n- Name Waste, Honor Purpose: Address concerns one-on-one with meeting leader.	59750382-b98f-4160-a00e-a1b2660d723a
a0cdf904-2e5a-44cd-9e17-3a1824814189	Christian	**Reports to:** Platform/Survey Operations Manager. \r\n\r\n# Goal\r\nProvide comprehensive First Party Assessment survey services that deliver actionable insights for church strategic planning and ministry effectiveness evaluation. \r\n\r\n# Key Responsibilities\r\n## Survey Creation & Customization\r\nCreate and customize FPA surveys based on specific church demographics, ministry focus areas, and strategic planning needs. Develop survey assets including implementation guides, best practices documentation, and technical setup instructions. Ensure survey design aligns with church culture (Catholic/Protestant) and community characteristics. \r\n## Distribution & Support\r\nSend complete survey packages to CSS including survey links, implementation guides, promotional materials, and technical support documentation. Provide guidance on effective survey launch strategies to ensure high completion rates and representative participation. \r\n## Monitoring & Reporting\r\nMonitor participation rates during survey periods with real-time tracking and engagement analytics. Send comprehensive participation reports to CSS after survey closure including demographic breakdowns, response rates, and preliminary insights. ## Responsive Support\r\nProvide participation updates upon CSS request during survey periods with detailed analytics and engagement patterns. Offer troubleshooting support for technical issues or low participation challenges. \r\n\r\n# Performance Standards\r\n- **Response Time:** 24-hour maximum for CSS requests, 48-hour maximum for survey creation and delivery.\r\n- **Quality Metrics:** Maintain survey completion rates above industry benchmarks, ensure data accuracy and reliability for strategic planning use.\r\n- **Meeting Rhythms:** Weekly coordination with CSS team for active surveys, monthly survey performance review and optimization planning, quarterly survey methodology and effectiveness analysis.	59750382-b98f-4160-a00e-a1b2660d723a
