87398231-5d31-4a6a-a565-1d729275ef20	Account Executive	## Function\nTurn interest into alignment  and alignment into signed, successful customers.\nThe Account Executive helps prospects understand what we solve, how we solve it, and what success looks like on both sides. They dont just close deals; they ensure every new client enters with clarity, confidence, and a clean handoff to Operations.\n\n## Excellence Looks Like\nSales doesnt feel like selling. It feels like matching.\nThe right customers come in with the right expectations, because discovery was thoughtful, proposals were precise, and handoffs were airtight.\nThe Account Executives pipeline runs clean  every deal is documented, priced correctly, and ready to deliver without rework or surprises.\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Conduct discovery sessions that uncover true business needs and constraints.\n- Draft clear, outcome-based proposals and Statements of Work.\n- Manage deal flow from first call through signed contract and payment.\n- Maintain accurate records and notes in the CRM for every interaction.\n- Coordinate with the Finance and Ops teams to ensure invoicing, kickoff, and expectations are aligned.\n- Run the Sales Handoff process to transition new clients to delivery smoothly.\n- Identify upsell or referral opportunities based on client goals and milestones.\n- Track and report on sales pipeline metrics, conversion rates, and revenue forecasts.\n\n## Metrics\n- **Win Rate**: % of qualified leads converted to paying customers.\n- **Cycle Time**: Average time from discovery to signed agreement.\n- **Data Hygiene**: Completeness and accuracy of CRM entries.\n- **Deal Quality**: % of projects that proceed without post-sale scope corrections.\n- **Customer Fit**: Retention and satisfaction rates of acquired clients.	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
27f03326-df38-4910-8999-d35e08b988d0	Accountant	## Function\nKeep the companys financial reality visible, accurate, and dependable.\nThe Accountant is the backbone of fiscal clarity  turning receipts, invoices, and transactions into a single source of truth that leadership and teams can trust to make decisions, plan growth, and stay compliant.\n\n## Excellence Looks Like\nMoney moves through the business cleanly and predictably.\nEvery cent is tracked, every account reconciled, every report arrives before anyone asks for it.\nThe numbers match reality  and leadership never has to wonder if the books are behind or the data is off.\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Maintain and reconcile the general ledger across all accounts and departments.\n- Manage Accounts Payable and Accounts Receivable with precision and consistency.\n- Coordinate with the Finance Coordinator on vendor payments and client billing cycles.\n- Support payroll processing and confirm that all taxes, deductions, and reimbursements post correctly.\n- Close the books monthly and prepare financial statements for review by the Finance Lead.\n- Monitor cash flow and flag emerging risks or anomalies early.\n- Maintain compliance with tax, payroll, and reporting requirements.\n- Partner with leadership to support audits, forecasting, and long-term financial planning.\n\n## Metrics\n- **Accuracy**: Zero unreconciled balances at close; no rework due to data errors.\n- **Timeliness**: Month-end close completed within five business days.\n- **Compliance**: All filings and remittances submitted by required deadlines.\n- **Clarity**: Reports delivered in plain English, not accounting jargon.\n- **Dependability**: Requests from leadership or auditors answered within one business day.	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
90555703-9a0d-4646-b302-239b4ecba0f8	Content Marketer	## Function\nTurn company insight into content that drives awareness, trust, and demand.\nThe Content Marketer translates strategy, process knowledge, and customer pain points into stories, visuals, and campaigns that help prospects understand why we exist and how we help.\n\n## Excellence Looks Like\nOur message is consistent, our tone is distinct, and our audience feels understood.\nEvery campaign connects to a real business outcome: traffic, subscribers, qualified leads.\nContent doesnt just fill channels; it builds reputation and creates demand that compounds.\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Plan and execute content calendars across owned channels (newsletter, website, social).\n- Write and publish content that communicates value and clarity  not jargon.\n- Collaborate with the Marketing Lead to align campaigns with positioning and goals.\n- Maintain a consistent voice and visual identity across formats and platforms.\n- Track engagement and conversion metrics to refine future content.\n- Repurpose internal process insights and customer stories into shareable, educational pieces.\n- Support the launch of new campaigns, offers, or features with appropriate assets.\n- Work with the Account Executive and Customer Success teams to surface proof points and testimonials.\n\n## Metrics\n- **Engagement** : Open, click, and share rates across core channels.\n- **Conversion**: % of content-driven leads that become qualified opportunities.\n- **Consistency**: Frequency and timeliness of scheduled content delivery.\n- **Reach**: Growth in subscribers, followers, or site visits within target audience.\n- **Alignment**: % of content mapped directly to company positioning or campaign objectives.	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
79caf76a-8bed-4645-bf72-3bb304154a28	Customer Success Lead	## Function\nEnsure every customer achieves the outcomes they bought, and sees a clear path to ongoing success.\nThe Customer Success Lead owns the relationship after delivery, guiding adoption, measuring satisfaction, and turning every successful engagement into retention, referrals, and expansion.\n\n## Excellence Looks Like\nCustomers dont just get what they paid for, they get what they hoped for.\nQuestions are answered before theyre asked. Renewals feel like formalities.\nThe Success Lead is the voice of the customer internally and the quiet confidence behind every satisfied client externally.\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Oversee onboarding and post-delivery follow-up for all new customers.\n- Monitor account health, usage, and feedback to identify risks or growth opportunities.\n- Conduct periodic check-ins and business reviews with key accounts.\n- Coordinate with Operations and Support to resolve issues quickly and permanently.\n- Maintain accurate customer records, notes, and renewal dates in the CRM.\n- Manage the Post-Delivery Follow-Up and Retention / Renewal processes.\n- Capture success stories, testimonials, and lessons learned for Marketing and Sales.\n- Report on customer sentiment trends and recommend process improvements.\n\n## Metrics\n**Retention**: % of customers renewing or remaining active.\n**Satisfaction**: Average survey score or NPS across accounts.\n**Response Time**: Average time to resolve customer-reported issues.\n**Expansion**: % of customers increasing spend or scope.\n**Advocacy**: Number of referrals, testimonials, or case studies generated.	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
0bcb0a46-ab63-4d9b-9abe-3f41cf205401	Customer Support Rep	## Function\nResolve customer issues quickly, clearly, and kindly.\nThe Customer Support Representative ensures every question, bug report, or request gets the right answer and that customers always feel heard, helped, and confident using our product or service.\n\n## Excellence Looks Like\nCustomers leave interactions calmer and more capable than when they arrived.\nTickets are handled fast, responses are consistent, and issues rarely bounce back.\nSupport isnt reactive. Its proactive, spotting patterns and helping the team prevent future problems before they start.\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Respond to customer inquiries via email, chat, or support portal within defined timeframes.\n- Diagnose issues, answer product or process questions, and guide users through solutions.\n- Escalate technical bugs or feature requests to the appropriate team through the Issue Resolution / Support process.\n- Track all interactions, resolutions, and sentiment in the helpdesk or CRM.\n- Maintain and update internal knowledge base and FAQ documentation.\n- Flag recurring issues or unclear documentation for Operations or Product review.\n- Follow up on resolved tickets to confirm customer satisfaction.\n- Participate in weekly support reviews to share insights and recommend improvements.\n\n## Metrics\n**Response Time**: Average time to first reply and full resolution.\n**Customer Satisfaction**: Post-interaction survey or rating scores.\n**Resolution Rate**: % of tickets solved without escalation or rework.\n**Knowledge Base Updates**: Number of new or revised articles contributed.\n**Feedback Loop**: Frequency of actionable insights shared with Ops or Product.	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
6376626f-951f-40ee-86ac-733e782f2d6a	Delivery Lead	## Function\nOwn the successful delivery of every client engagement from kickoff to completion.\nThe Delivery Lead translates contracts into outcomes, coordinating people, systems, and timelines so that projects finish on time, within scope, and to standard.\nTheyre the steward of both client satisfaction and internal execution discipline.\n\n## Excellence Looks Like\nEvery project starts clearly, runs smoothly, and ends cleanly.\nClients know exactly whats happening and when.\nTeam members know what theyre responsible for and deliver their best work without chaos or guesswork.\nThe Delivery Lead doesnt simply manage timelines, they protect the companys reputation for reliable, high-quality delivery.\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Oversee project setup, ensuring scope, timeline, and resources are clearly defined.\n- Lead internal and client kickoff meetings to align on goals, deliverables, and communication cadence.\n- Manage progress through the Project Setup, Production / Implementation, and Quality Assurance processes.\n- Coordinate team workloads, priorities, and dependencies across active projects.\n- Communicate proactively with clients on status, risks, and next steps.\n- Monitor quality standards, flag risks early, and ensure corrective action.\n- Close out completed projects with final reviews, documentation, and client feedback.\n- Collaborate with Finance on invoicing milestones and delivery confirmations.\n\n## Metrics\n**On-Time Delivery**: % of projects completed within planned timeline.\n**On-Budget Execution**: Variance between estimated and actual labor or cost.\n**Client Satisfaction**: Average feedback score from post-delivery surveys.\n**Internal Efficiency**: Average turnaround time from intake to completion.\n**Quality**: % of deliverables passing QA on first review.	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
