20df3e8c-bb2f-4dd0-befa-67e56409b3d0	Amazon Quicksight	## Function\nAmazon QuickSight is our business intelligence (BI) and analytics platform.\nIt connects to our data sources and turns them into dashboards, reports, and visual insights that support decision-making across Finance, Operations, and Leadership.\n\n## Purpose in the Business\nQuickSight helps us see our business performance  not just record it.\nIt centralizes metrics like revenue, expenses, client delivery timelines, and retention rates so that leaders and teams can make informed, data-driven decisions without manually exporting spreadsheets or running ad-hoc queries.\n\n## Primary Uses\n- Build and share interactive dashboards using live data.\n- Track KPIs from accounting (e.g., revenue, expenses, margins).\n- Visualize operational performance (e.g., delivery timelines, QA pass rates).\n- Monitor marketing and sales funnels via connected CRM or analytics sources.\n- Automate scheduled reports for monthly or quarterly reviews.\n\n## Access & Ownership\n- System Owner: Finance Lead (admin access)\n- Collaborators: Operations Lead, Marketing Lead, Leadership\n- Access Type: View or author permissions granted by request through IT or the Finance Lead.\n- Data Sources: Typically connects to AWS data lakes, spreadsheets in S3, or third-party sources (QuickBooks, HubSpot, etc.).\n\n## Best Practices\n- Use shared dashboards whenever possible  avoid duplicating visualizations.\n- Apply consistent naming conventions (e.g., Finance - Monthly Report, Ops - Delivery Performance).\n- Validate data connections quarterly to prevent broken or stale sources.\n- Restrict author privileges to trained users to maintain dashboard integrity.\n- Reference QuickSight_Visualization_Standards.md before publishing new dashboards.	https://aws.amazon.com/quicksuite/quicksight/	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
2a0ead38-7ac7-4c9d-ac3f-9c4cc19a63d9	Gusto	## Gusto\n\n## Function  \nGusto is our payroll, benefits, and HR management platform.  \nIt handles employee and contractor payments, tax filings, and essential onboarding paperwork from one central dashboard.\n\n## Purpose in the Business  \nGusto ensures every team member is paid accurately and on time while keeping all payroll taxes, filings, and employment records compliant.  \nIt also simplifies new hire onboarding, document collection, and benefits administration so HR tasks stay organized and repeatable.\n\n## Primary Uses  \n- Run payroll for employees and contractors each pay period.  \n- Automatically calculate, file, and remit federal and state payroll taxes.  \n- Generate pay slips and year-end tax documents (e.g., W-2, 1099).  \n- Manage employee profiles, job details, and compensation records.  \n- Collect and store onboarding documents such as W-4 and I-9 forms.  \n- Track PTO, sick leave, and time-off requests.  \n- Manage benefits, reimbursements, and company contributions.\n\n## Access & Ownership  \n- System Owner: Finance Lead (admin access)  \n- Collaborators: HR Lead, Accountant, Finance Coordinator  \n- Access Type: Role-based permissions managed by the Finance Lead.  \n- Data Sources: Employee and contractor information, compensation details, and tax identifiers.\n\n## Best Practices  \n- Confirm hours and compensation details before each payroll run.  \n- Review payroll preview reports carefully before approving payment.  \n- Ensure all new hires complete onboarding forms within Gusto prior to their first pay date.  \n- Verify tax filings and deposits after each payroll cycle.  \n- Use standardized naming and organization for departments and job titles.  \n- Archive year-end reports and tax documents in secure shared storage.	gusto.com	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
63f2e3a2-1cd2-4d40-a691-e4ecd16aae9e	HubSpot	## HubSpot\n\n## Function  \nHubSpot is our customer relationship management (CRM) platform.  \nIt centralizes all sales, marketing, and customer interactions so we can track leads, manage pipelines, and maintain consistent communication with prospects and clients.\n\n## Purpose in the Business  \nHubSpot acts as the single source of truth for customer data and activity.  \nIt allows teams to see the full lifecycle of each relationship  from initial contact to closed deal and ongoing account management  without scattered spreadsheets or lost emails.\n\n## Primary Uses  \n- Manage leads, deals, and accounts through defined sales stages.  \n- Log emails, calls, and meetings with prospects and clients.  \n- Automate marketing follow-ups and nurture sequences.  \n- Track lead sources and campaign attribution.  \n- Maintain up-to-date customer contact information and history.  \n- Generate pipeline and conversion reports for leadership review.\n\n## Access & Ownership  \n- System Owner: Sales Lead (admin access)  \n- Collaborators: Account Executives, Marketing Lead, Customer Success Lead  \n- Access Type: User permissions assigned by Sales Lead or IT support.  \n- Data Sources: Lead forms, email integrations, marketing imports, and manual entries.\n\n## Best Practices  \n- Always update lead and deal stages in real time to maintain CRM accuracy.  \n- Record every significant client interaction directly in HubSpot.  \n- Use standardized naming conventions for deals and tasks (e.g., ClientName - PackageType - MonthYear).  \n- Sync HubSpot with marketing forms and newsletters to capture inbound leads automatically.  \n- Review pipeline weekly to archive stalled or duplicate records.  \n- Restrict admin privileges to trained staff to maintain data integrity.	hubspot.com	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
aef24997-2ff6-4b7d-a985-73b7d27379c9	SignWell	## SignWell\n\n## Function  \nSignWell is our electronic signature platform.  \nIt provides a fast, legally compliant way to send, sign, and track agreements such as proposals, contracts, and onboarding documents.\n\n## Purpose in the Business  \nSignWell replaces manual or paper-based signing with a streamlined, secure process.  \nIt ensures every documentwhether internal or client-facingis signed, stored, and auditable without delays or confusion.\n\n## Primary Uses  \n- Send proposals, Statements of Work, and service agreements for signature.  \n- Collect client or contractor signatures quickly from any device.  \n- Store signed documents with complete audit trails and timestamps.  \n- Use reusable templates for recurring agreements like NDAs or onboarding forms.  \n- Track document status (sent, viewed, signed, completed) in real time.  \n- Download and archive finalized documents for recordkeeping.\n\n## Access & Ownership  \n- System Owner: Operations Lead (admin access)  \n- Collaborators: Account Executives, Delivery Lead, HR / Finance staff as needed  \n- Access Type: User accounts managed by the Operations Lead; templates and folders organized by department.  \n- Data Sources: Uploaded PDF or DOCX templates stored in the shared drive.\n\n## Best Practices  \n- Always use approved templates for proposals and contracts to ensure consistency.  \n- Double-check signer names and email addresses before sending.  \n- Add yourself as a CC recipient on every outgoing signature request.  \n- Store completed documents in the appropriate client or HR folder within shared storage.  \n- Use descriptive file names (e.g., ClientName - SOW - YYYY-MM-DD).  \n- Periodically review template library to retire outdated versions.	https://www.signwell.com/	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
24d5ca4d-5051-4a16-aed5-ecd3a889e7bf	Monday	## Function  \nMonday.com is our collaborative work management platform.  \nIt provides a centralized place to plan, assign, and track tasks, projects, and deliverables across teams.\n\n## Purpose in the Business  \nMonday.com keeps operational work visible and organized.  \nIt ensures every project has clear owners, deadlines, and progress tracking, reducing dependency on email threads or ad-hoc updates.  \nBy standardizing workflows, it helps teams move faster, communicate clearly, and deliver consistently.\n\n## Primary Uses  \n- Create and manage project boards for client work, marketing campaigns, and internal initiatives.  \n- Assign tasks, due dates, and priorities to specific team members.  \n- Track project stages from intake through completion.  \n- Maintain visibility into active workloads, blockers, and upcoming deadlines.  \n- Integrate with communication tools (Slack, Gmail) for automatic updates.  \n- Record notes, attachments, and progress within each item for transparent collaboration.  \n- Generate simple progress and performance reports for leadership reviews.\n\n## Access & Ownership  \n- System Owner: Operations Lead (admin access)  \n- Collaborators: All department leads and team members with project responsibilities.  \n- Access Type: Role-based permissions; board access granted by project or department.  \n- Data Sources: Task assignments, client project data, and linked documents.\n\n## Best Practices  \n- Use existing templates when creating new project boards to ensure consistency.  \n- Keep task titles short, action-oriented, and clear.  \n- Update task status daily to reflect real progress.  \n- Use comments for context, not for decisions that belong in Quaestor or official documentation.  \n- Archive completed projects promptly to maintain system performance.  \n- Review dashboards weekly to monitor overdue tasks and workload balance.  	monday.com	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
fd9223a2-087a-42d6-8f44-fb68b9573a32	PandaDoc	## Function  \nPandaDoc is our proposal and contract platform.  \nIt allows us to create, send, and track proposals, Statements of Work, and agreements with clients in a polished, repeatable format.\n\n## Purpose in the Business  \nPandaDoc streamlines how deals move from verbal agreement to signed contract.  \nIt ensures every proposal and SOW is consistent, on-brand, and traceable  with visibility into when documents are viewed, signed, or pending.\n\n## Primary Uses  \n- Create proposal and contract templates with standardized pricing, scope, and terms.  \n- Send proposals and agreements directly to clients for e-signature.  \n- Track document status in real time (sent, viewed, signed, completed).  \n- Store signed copies automatically for compliance and recordkeeping.  \n- Use dynamic variables (client name, price, date) to auto-fill key fields.  \n- Integrate with SignWell for signature collection and HubSpot for deal tracking.\n\n## Access & Ownership  \n- System Owner: Sales Lead (admin access)  \n- Collaborators: Account Executives, Delivery Lead, Finance Coordinator  \n- Access Type: Role-based permissions; templates managed by Sales Lead.  \n- Data Sources: Pricing sheets, contract templates, and client details from HubSpot or shared storage.\n\n## Best Practices  \n- Always start from an approved template to maintain consistent structure and legal language.  \n- Double-check scope, pricing, and dates before sending any document.  \n- Use version control for any edits to standard terms.  \n- CC the Delivery Lead or Finance when proposals include implementation or billing details.  \n- Archive finalized and signed proposals in the clients project folder.  \n- Review and refresh template content quarterly to keep terms current.\n	pandadoc.com	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
3273106a-45ac-4b48-9973-0c23524d1ebd	BambooHR	## Function  \nBamboo is our Human Resources Information System (HRIS).  \nIt serves as the central record for employee data, job history, performance reviews, and HR documentation.\n\n## Purpose in the Business  \nBamboo maintains a single, accurate source of truth for all employee information.  \nIt supports the full employee lifecyclefrom hiring and onboarding through reviews, promotions, and offboardingensuring consistency and compliance across the organizations.\n\n## Primary Uses  \n- Store and manage employee profiles, positions, and compensation details.  \n- Track start dates, promotions, and employment changes.  \n- Record and schedule performance reviews and one-on-one meetings.  \n- Manage company policies, handbooks, and signed HR documents.  \n- Track PTO, sick leave, and absences.  \n- Generate organization charts and headcount reports.  \n- Integrate with Gusto for seamless payroll and benefits updates.\n\n## Access & Ownership  \n- System Owner: HR Lead (admin access)  \n- Collaborators: Finance Lead, Department Leads  \n- Access Type: Role-based permissions with HR controlling access to sensitive data.  \n- Data Sources: Employee records, onboarding forms, and review documentation.\n\n## Best Practices  \n- Keep employee data updated within 24 hours of any change (title, pay, status).  \n- Schedule quarterly review cycles and document all feedback within the platform.  \n- Store signed policy acknowledgments and HR forms directly in Humi.  \n- Verify permissions regularly to maintain data privacy.  \n- Export and archive key reports annually for compliance purposes.  	bamboohr.com	28fb29e6-1f37-4b73-98ce-fdad0aebc73c
